{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n \\\"test_generation_failed|test generation|generate.*test|Human intervention|failed|ERROR|exception|N/A|repository-url|test-code-url\\\" human-intervention-logs build .github forge skills -g '\"'!**/.git/**'\"'\"","aggregated_output":"skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:3:description: Review automated pull requests with the `library-bulk-update` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that bumps tested versions for existing libraries, including approve vs close decisions, CI checks, diff-scope validation, and verification of `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` changes.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:15:- Close the PR when it contains unrelated changes such as workflow files, Gradle files, generated sources, or test code that clearly did not belong in a bulk version update.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:24:   - Read the body and verify it is a bot-generated \"Added tested versions\" summary.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:47:   - If checks failed because the PR is contaminated by unrelated changes, close it.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:48:   - If checks failed due to likely infra flakiness or a suspicious runner issue, request a rerun or rerun all relevant tests before approval.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:57:   - Review `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` with the same rules used by `PopulateArtifactURLs`.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:67:- `repository-url` is the canonical repository root URL.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:68:- `repository-url` must not include a versioned tree path such as `/tree/<tag>`.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:69:- `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` must point to the exact library version in the changed entry.\nskills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:97:- The diff looks correct but CI failed in a way that smells like infrastructure noise.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect runtime-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, dependency adjustments, runtime configuration, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:46:   - Reject or request changes if the PR removes tests, disables test classes, catches and ignores the failing exception, or disables native-image behavior.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Confirm the edit addresses the actual JVM runtime failure, such as changed runtime behavior, missing test resources, service loading changes, dependency conflicts, classpath/module issues, initialization order, changed exception types, or changed API semantics that only fail during execution.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:   - Test expectation changes are acceptable only when they still assert meaningful behavior for the new version instead of accepting any output or exception.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:93:- The fix makes JVM tests pass by deleting tests, skipping execution, swallowing the failing exception.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:102:- CI failed in a way that looks like infrastructure noise.\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:113:- For swallowed exceptions: say that catching or ignoring the failing exception hides the runtime failure instead of proving the library behavior works.\n.github/actions/setup-native-build-tools/action.yml:81:            echo \"git ls-remote failed (network or repo issue). Using fallback: ${INPUT_FALLBACK_REF}\"\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:40:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Test changes are acceptable when the upstream API or runtime behavior changed, but they must still exercise the native path that previously failed.\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:99:- CI failed in a way that looks like infrastructure noise.\nskills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:23:- Treat `0/0` dynamic-access coverage as a valid no-calls case, not as failed coverage. Do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata; those stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\nskills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:42:   - Be suspicious of changes to build logic, workflows, unrelated libraries, generated sources outside the target test directory, or wide refactors.\nskills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect compile-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, imports, renamed APIs, dependency adjustments, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\nskills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `bu